  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-5 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Ten factors are fully assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels; three factors (numerical solver error, use error, and equivalency of input parameters) are scoped out with documented rationale. All assessed factors carry acceptance criteria and provenance-linked validation results. Decision: Accepted.",
